WEBVTT

1
00:00:53.428 --> 00:00:55.430
(Beeping)

2
00:01:23.917 --> 00:01:25.210
Wait for it.

3
00:01:25.877 --> 00:01:27.963
- Can I turn on the radio?
- No.

4
00:01:32.426 --> 00:01:34.928
Erik: Jane. you can't keep doing this.

5
00:01:35.929 --> 00:01:39.516
The last 17 occurrences
have been predictable to the second.

6
00:01:39.600 --> 00:01:42.352
Erik: Jane. you're an astrophysicist.
not some storm chaser.

7
00:01:42.436 --> 00:01:44.313
Jane: I'm telling you.
there's a connection

8
00:01:44.396 --> 00:01:47.190
between these atmospheric
disturbances and my research.

9
00:01:47.274 --> 00:01:51.737
Erik. I wouldn't have asked you to
fly out here if I wasn't absolutely sure.

10
00:01:51.987 --> 00:01:53.196
Darcy: Jane?

11
00:01:53.947 --> 00:01:55.240
I think you want to see this.

12
00:01:59.661 --> 00:02:00.661
Jane: What is that?

13
00:02:08.003 --> 00:02:10.380
Erik: I thought you said
it was a subtle Aurora!

14
00:02:18.889 --> 00:02:21.016
- Get closer.
- Right. Good one.

15
00:02:27.648 --> 00:02:28.648
(Laughing)

16
00:02:31.318 --> 00:02:32.653
(All exclaiming)

17
00:02:39.951 --> 00:02:41.161
What are you doing?

18
00:02:41.244 --> 00:02:44.414
I am not dying for six college credits!

19
00:02:44.498 --> 00:02:45.916
(Darcy exclaiming)

20
00:02:48.669 --> 00:02:49.669
(Thunder crashing)

21
00:02:51.338 --> 00:02:52.589
(Darcy and Jane exclaiming)

22
00:02:56.718 --> 00:02:57.718
(Gasps)

23
00:03:05.519 --> 00:03:07.239
Darcy: I think that was legally your fault.

24
00:03:07.312 --> 00:03:09.064
Jane: Get the first aid kit.

25
00:03:09.147 --> 00:03:10.607
Do me a favor and don't be dead.

26
00:03:10.691 --> 00:03:12.150
Please.

27
00:03:17.531 --> 00:03:18.949
Where did he come from?

28
00:03:36.717 --> 00:03:38.385
Odin: Once.

29
00:03:38.468 --> 00:03:42.222
mankind accepted a simple truth.

30
00:03:42.305 --> 00:03:45.976
that they were not alone in this universe.

31
00:03:47.936 --> 00:03:51.690
Some worlds man believed
to be home to their gods.

32
00:03:52.524 --> 00:03:55.110
Others. they knew to fear.

33
00:03:58.864 --> 00:04:03.160
From a realm of cold and darkness
came the frost giants.

34
00:04:15.547 --> 00:04:16.673
(Screams)

35
00:04:17.215 --> 00:04:20.761
Threatening to plunge the mortal world
into a new ice age.

36
00:04:20.844 --> 00:04:21.928
(Roars)

37
00:04:27.142 --> 00:04:31.813
But humanity
would not face this threat alone.

38
00:04:45.744 --> 00:04:46.995
(Yelling)

39
00:05:08.266 --> 00:05:12.771
Our armies drove the frost giants
back into the heart of their own world.

40
00:05:16.191 --> 00:05:18.360
The cost was great.

41
00:05:19.110 --> 00:05:20.779
In the end.

42
00:05:20.862 --> 00:05:22.906
their king fell.

43
00:05:27.285 --> 00:05:30.288
And the source of their power
was taken from them.

44
00:05:31.665 --> 00:05:33.917
With the last great war ended.

45
00:05:34.000 --> 00:05:37.587
we withdrew from the other worlds
and returned home

46
00:05:38.463 --> 00:05:40.632
to the realm eternal.

47
00:05:41.967 --> 00:05:43.635
asgard.

48
00:06:15.166 --> 00:06:17.794
Here we remain as a beacon of hope.

49
00:06:19.004 --> 00:06:21.840
shining out across the stars.

50
00:06:22.841 --> 00:06:26.136
And though we have fallen
into man's myths and legends.

51
00:06:27.512 --> 00:06:29.764
it was asgard

52
00:06:29.848 --> 00:06:31.850
and its warriors

53
00:06:31.933 --> 00:06:33.184
that brought peace

54
00:06:34.102 --> 00:06:35.186
to the universe.

55
00:06:39.190 --> 00:06:41.860
But the day will come

56
00:06:43.403 --> 00:06:44.738
when one of you

57
00:06:45.864 --> 00:06:47.657
will have to defend that peace.

58
00:06:48.408 --> 00:06:50.327
Do the frost giants still live?

59
00:06:50.911 --> 00:06:51.912
When I'm king.

60
00:06:52.913 --> 00:06:55.624
I'll hunt the monsters down
and slay them all!

61
00:06:57.042 --> 00:06:58.293
Just as you did. father.

62
00:06:59.127 --> 00:07:00.712
A wise king

63
00:07:01.212 --> 00:07:03.798
never seeks out war.

64
00:07:04.341 --> 00:07:05.342
But...

65
00:07:10.055 --> 00:07:12.307
He must always be ready for it.

66
00:07:24.110 --> 00:07:26.571
- I'm ready. father.
- So am I.

67
00:07:27.739 --> 00:07:30.367
Only one of you can ascend
to the throne.

68
00:07:30.450 --> 00:07:34.162
But both of you were born to be kings.

69
00:07:34.746 --> 00:07:36.498
(All cheering)

70
00:07:55.016 --> 00:07:56.601
Oh. please.

71
00:08:12.575 --> 00:08:13.827
Yeah!

72
00:08:45.150 --> 00:08:46.735
(Spear thudding)

73
00:08:53.491 --> 00:08:56.661
Thor odinson.

74
00:08:58.747 --> 00:08:59.831
myhdn

75
00:09:02.876 --> 00:09:04.794
my firstborn.

76
00:09:05.837 --> 00:09:10.300
So long entrusted with
the mighty hammer Mjolnir.

77
00:09:10.759 --> 00:09:14.054
forged in the heart of a dying star.

78
00:09:14.804 --> 00:09:17.015
its power has no equal.

79
00:09:17.515 --> 00:09:19.976
as a weapon to destroy

80
00:09:20.518 --> 00:09:22.353
or as a tool to build.

81
00:09:23.396 --> 00:09:25.648
'Tis a fit companion for a king.

82
00:09:27.650 --> 00:09:30.236
I have defended asgard

83
00:09:30.320 --> 00:09:34.407
and the lives of the innocent
across the nine realms

84
00:09:34.491 --> 00:09:36.576
from the time of the great beginning.

85
00:09:37.410 --> 00:09:38.995
Though the day has come...

86
00:10:05.688 --> 00:10:08.441
Do you swear to guard the nine realms?

87
00:10:08.942 --> 00:10:09.943
I swear.

88
00:10:10.026 --> 00:10:13.446
And do you swear
to preserve the peace?

89
00:10:13.530 --> 00:10:14.572
I swear.

90
00:10:15.115 --> 00:10:16.950
Do you swear

91
00:10:18.159 --> 00:10:20.537
to cast aside all selfish ambition

92
00:10:20.620 --> 00:10:23.540
and to pledge yourself only
to the good of the realms?

93
00:10:23.623 --> 00:10:24.623
I swear!

94
00:10:24.958 --> 00:10:27.085
Then. on this day.

95
00:10:27.502 --> 00:10:30.130
I. Odin all father.

96
00:10:31.631 --> 00:10:33.174
proclaim you...

97
00:10:43.518 --> 00:10:45.687
({shouts) {Grunts)

98
00:10:46.855 --> 00:10:48.064
The frost giants!

99
00:11:00.076 --> 00:11:01.244
(Spear thudding)

100
00:11:33.359 --> 00:11:35.320
Thor: The jotuns must pay
for what they've done!

101
00:11:35.403 --> 00:11:37.739
They have paid. with their lives.

102
00:11:39.199 --> 00:11:40.909
The destroyer did its work.

103
00:11:41.367 --> 00:11:43.244
the casket is safe. and all is well.

104
00:11:43.745 --> 00:11:44.871
All is well?

105
00:11:45.788 --> 00:11:48.124
They broke into the weapons vault!

106
00:11:48.541 --> 00:11:50.822
If the frost giants had stolen
even one of these relics...

107
00:11:50.877 --> 00:11:53.213
- They didn't.
- Well. I want to know why!

108
00:11:56.090 --> 00:11:58.259
I have a truce with laufey.
king of the jotuns.

109
00:11:58.343 --> 00:12:02.847
He just broke your truce!
They know you are vulnerable!

110
00:12:03.640 --> 00:12:04.849
What action would you take?

111
00:12:04.933 --> 00:12:08.311
March into Jotunheim as you once did.
Teach them a lesson.

112
00:12:08.937 --> 00:12:09.812
Break their spirits

113
00:12:09.896 --> 00:12:12.023
so they'll never dare
try to cross our borders again.

114
00:12:12.106 --> 00:12:13.459
You're thinking only as a warrior.

115
00:12:13.483 --> 00:12:14.692
This was an act of war!

116
00:12:14.776 --> 00:12:17.070
It was the act of but a few.
doomed to fail.

117
00:12:17.153 --> 00:12:18.655
Look how far they got!

118
00:12:18.738 --> 00:12:21.199
We will find the breach in our defenses
and it will be sealed.

119
00:12:21.282 --> 00:12:22.533
As king of asgard...

120
00:12:22.617 --> 00:12:25.411
But you're not king!

121
00:12:28.498 --> 00:12:29.582
Not yet.

122
00:12:41.427 --> 00:12:42.971
(Roaring)

123
00:13:01.447 --> 00:13:04.492
It's unwise to be in my company
right now. brother.

124
00:13:05.493 --> 00:13:08.329
This was to be my day of triumph.

125
00:13:10.540 --> 00:13:11.874
It'll come.

126
00:13:13.167 --> 00:13:14.460
In time.

127
00:13:14.544 --> 00:13:16.838
What's this?

128
00:13:18.298 --> 00:13:21.384
If it's any consolation. I think you're right.

129
00:13:21.467 --> 00:13:24.304
About the frost giants.
about laufey. about everything.

130
00:13:25.221 --> 00:13:28.266
If they found a way to penetrate
asgard's defenses once.

131
00:13:28.349 --> 00:13:29.892
who's to say they won't try again?

132
00:13:29.976 --> 00:13:32.061
- Next time with an army.
- Exactly.

133
00:13:32.145 --> 00:13:34.939
There's nothing you can do
without defying father.

134
00:13:37.066 --> 00:13:38.943
No. no. no. I know that look.

135
00:13:39.027 --> 00:13:41.171
That's the only way
to ensure the safety of our borders.

136
00:13:41.195 --> 00:13:42.322
Thor. it's madness.

137
00:13:42.739 --> 00:13:45.283
Madness? What sort of madness?

138
00:13:45.992 --> 00:13:47.618
We're going to Jotunheim.

139
00:13:49.329 --> 00:13:50.329
Volstagg: What?

140
00:13:50.747 --> 00:13:52.498
This isn't like a journey to earth

141
00:13:52.582 --> 00:13:54.625
where you summon
a little lightning and thunder.

142
00:13:54.709 --> 00:13:56.669
and the mortals worship you as a god.

143
00:13:57.503 --> 00:13:58.796
This is Jotunheim.

144
00:13:58.880 --> 00:14:01.174
My father fought his way into Jotunheim.

145
00:14:01.257 --> 00:14:03.968
defeated their armies
and took their casket.

146
00:14:04.510 --> 00:14:05.821
We would just be looking for answers.

147
00:14:05.845 --> 00:14:07.138
It is forbidden!

148
00:14:07.930 --> 00:14:09.307
(Chuckles)

149
00:14:09.766 --> 00:14:12.435
My friends. have you forgotten
all that we have done together?

150
00:14:12.769 --> 00:14:14.604
Fandral. ho gun.

151
00:14:14.687 --> 00:14:17.523
Who led you
into the most glorious of battles?

152
00:14:18.483 --> 00:14:19.484
You did.

153
00:14:19.776 --> 00:14:21.944
And volstagg. to delicacies so succulent.

154
00:14:22.028 --> 00:14:24.614
you thought you'd died
and gone to Valhalla?

155
00:14:24.697 --> 00:14:25.948
(Laughs)

156
00:14:26.199 --> 00:14:27.033
You did.

157
00:14:27.116 --> 00:14:28.117
Yes!

158
00:14:28.201 --> 00:14:30.161
And who proved wrong
all who scoffed at the idea

159
00:14:30.244 --> 00:14:32.705
that a young maiden could be
one of the fiercest warriors

160
00:14:32.789 --> 00:14:33.998
this realm has ever known?

161
00:14:34.082 --> 00:14:35.082
I did.

162
00:14:35.541 --> 00:14:37.377
True. but I supported you. sif.

163
00:14:37.960 --> 00:14:39.337
My friends.

164
00:14:39.754 --> 00:14:41.506
we're going to Jotunheim.

165
00:15:33.182 --> 00:15:34.183
You leave this to me.

166
00:15:35.852 --> 00:15:38.479
- Good Heimdall...
- You're not dressed warmly enough.

167
00:15:38.563 --> 00:15:39.647
I'm sorry?

168
00:15:39.730 --> 00:15:42.567
Do you think that you can deceive me?

169
00:15:43.484 --> 00:15:45.444
- (Laughs) You must be mistaken...
- Thor: Enough!

170
00:15:48.698 --> 00:15:50.241
Heimdall. may we pass?

171
00:15:50.616 --> 00:15:56.831
Never has an enemy slipped my watch
until this day.

172
00:15:58.666 --> 00:16:00.293
I wish to know how that happened.

173
00:16:00.376 --> 00:16:03.045
Then tell no one where we have gone
until we've returned.

174
00:16:03.129 --> 00:16:04.922
Understand?

175
00:16:09.343 --> 00:16:11.596
What happened?
Silver tongue turn to lead?

176
00:16:11.679 --> 00:16:13.264
(All laughing)

177
00:16:56.599 --> 00:16:57.599
Heimdall: Be warned.

178
00:16:58.184 --> 00:17:02.355
I will honor my sworn oath
to protect this realm as its gatekeeper.

179
00:17:03.105 --> 00:17:05.983
If your return
threatens the safety of asgard.

180
00:17:06.067 --> 00:17:08.277
Bifrost will remain closed to you

181
00:17:08.819 --> 00:17:11.822
and you'll be left to die
in the cold waste of Jotunheim.

182
00:17:11.906 --> 00:17:13.926
Volstagg: Couldn't you just
leave the bridge open for us?

183
00:17:13.950 --> 00:17:15.310
Heimdall: To leave the bridge open

184
00:17:15.368 --> 00:17:17.495
would unleash
the full power of the Bifrost

185
00:17:17.578 --> 00:17:20.706
and destroy Jotunheim with you upon it.

186
00:17:21.249 --> 00:17:22.833
I have no plans to die today.

187
00:17:23.125 --> 00:17:24.335
None do.

188
00:18:10.798 --> 00:18:12.091
We shouldn't be here.

189
00:18:14.510 --> 00:18:16.137
Let's move.

190
00:19:14.987 --> 00:19:16.322
Where are they?

191
00:19:16.405 --> 00:19:17.740
Hiding.

192
00:19:17.823 --> 00:19:19.408
as cowards always do.

193
00:19:29.835 --> 00:19:34.048
Laufey: You've come a long way to die.
asgardians.

194
00:19:34.131 --> 00:19:36.759
I am Thor odinson!

195
00:19:36.842 --> 00:19:38.803
Laufey: We know who you are.

196
00:19:39.095 --> 00:19:41.389
How did your people get into asgard?

197
00:19:47.186 --> 00:19:49.021
(Exhales slowly)

198
00:19:50.856 --> 00:19:54.902
The house of Odin is full of traitors.

199
00:19:54.985 --> 00:19:58.239
Do not dishonor my father's name
with your lies!

200
00:19:58.322 --> 00:20:01.450
Your father is a murderer and a thief!

201
00:20:01.701 --> 00:20:04.912
And why have you come here?
To make peace?

202
00:20:05.204 --> 00:20:08.249
You long for battle. You crave it.

203
00:20:08.916 --> 00:20:10.793
You're nothing but a boy

204
00:20:11.085 --> 00:20:13.546
trying to prove himself a man.

205
00:20:14.922 --> 00:20:18.259
Thor: Well. this "boy"
has grown tired of your mockery.

206
00:20:24.974 --> 00:20:27.560
Thor. stop and think.

207
00:20:27.643 --> 00:20:29.145
Look around you. we're outnumbered.

208
00:20:29.228 --> 00:20:30.855
Know your place. brother.

209
00:20:30.938 --> 00:20:34.191
You know not
what your actions would unleash.

210
00:20:37.319 --> 00:20:38.571
I do.

211
00:20:39.488 --> 00:20:43.409
Go now. while I still allow it.

212
00:20:54.336 --> 00:20:57.590
We will accept your most gracious offer.

213
00:21:07.433 --> 00:21:08.851
(Grunts)

214
00:21:10.144 --> 00:21:11.604
Come now. brother.

215
00:21:17.109 --> 00:21:19.320
Frost giant:
Run back home. little Princess.

216
00:21:19.945 --> 00:21:20.945
Damn.

217
00:21:26.285 --> 00:21:27.453
Next?

218
00:21:36.545 --> 00:21:37.546
(Laughing)

219
00:21:39.799 --> 00:21:41.008
(Yelling)

220
00:21:46.597 --> 00:21:48.849
At least make it a challenge for me!

221
00:21:57.817 --> 00:21:58.901
(Roaring)

222
00:21:58.984 --> 00:21:59.985
(Roaring)

223
00:22:03.614 --> 00:22:04.615
(Laughing)

224
00:22:09.245 --> 00:22:10.830
That's more like it.

225
00:22:22.675 --> 00:22:24.343
(Shouting)

226
00:22:41.527 --> 00:22:42.528
(Yells)

227
00:22:44.405 --> 00:22:45.406
(Groans)

228
00:22:46.615 --> 00:22:47.825
Don't let them touch you!

229
00:23:11.348 --> 00:23:12.433
(Laughing)

230
00:23:25.279 --> 00:23:26.405
(Screams)

231
00:23:29.950 --> 00:23:31.327
Thor!

232
00:23:33.287 --> 00:23:35.289
- We must go!
- Then go!

233
00:23:49.094 --> 00:23:50.554
(Rumbling)

234
00:23:59.021 --> 00:24:00.314
Run!

235
00:24:02.483 --> 00:24:03.817
Thor!

236
00:24:10.574 --> 00:24:11.575
(Roars)

237
00:24:53.659 --> 00:24:55.035
(Laughing)

238
00:25:09.466 --> 00:25:10.884
Heimdall!

239
00:25:11.218 --> 00:25:13.012
Open the bridge!

240
00:25:20.561 --> 00:25:21.603
(Roaring)

241
00:26:12.988 --> 00:26:14.323
(Horse whinnying)

242
00:26:18.327 --> 00:26:21.038
Father! We'll finish them together!

243
00:26:21.121 --> 00:26:22.623
Silence!

244
00:26:28.337 --> 00:26:29.755
Allfather.

245
00:26:31.256 --> 00:26:33.467
You look weary.

246
00:26:35.302 --> 00:26:36.386
Laufey.

247
00:26:36.845 --> 00:26:38.639
end this now.

248
00:26:38.722 --> 00:26:40.766
Your boy sought this out.

249
00:26:41.725 --> 00:26:42.893
You're right.

250
00:26:44.311 --> 00:26:47.189
And these are the actions of a boy.
treat them as such.

251
00:26:48.148 --> 00:26:52.528
You and I can end this here and now.
before there's further bloodshed.

252
00:26:52.611 --> 00:26:55.823
We are beyond diplomacy now. all father.

253
00:26:57.699 --> 00:26:59.159
He'll get what he came for.

254
00:27:00.494 --> 00:27:01.495
War

255
00:27:01.870 --> 00:27:03.205
and death.

256
00:27:04.790 --> 00:27:06.125
So be it.

257
00:27:30.190 --> 00:27:31.066
Thor: Why did you bring us back?

258
00:27:31.150 --> 00:27:32.168
Odin: Do you realize what you've done?

259
00:27:32.192 --> 00:27:34.087
- What you've started?
- Thor: I was protecting my home.

260
00:27:34.111 --> 00:27:35.713
Odin: You cannot even protect
your friends!

261
00:27:35.737 --> 00:27:37.489
How can you hope to protect a kingdom?

262
00:27:37.573 --> 00:27:39.283
Get him to the healing room! Now!

263
00:27:39.366 --> 00:27:42.703
Thor: There won't be a kingdom
to protect if you're afraid to act.

264
00:27:44.121 --> 00:27:48.000
The jotuns must learn to fear me.
just as they once feared you.

265
00:27:48.083 --> 00:27:50.502
Odin: That's pride and vanity talking.
not leadership.

266
00:27:50.586 --> 00:27:53.589
You've forgotten everything I taught you
about a warrior's Patience.

267
00:27:53.672 --> 00:27:57.342
While you wait and be patient.
the nine realms laugh at us.

268
00:27:57.801 --> 00:27:58.802
The old ways are done.

269
00:27:58.886 --> 00:28:01.513
You'd stand giving speeches
while asgard falls.

270
00:28:01.597 --> 00:28:05.142
You are a vain. greedy. cruel boy!

271
00:28:05.225 --> 00:28:08.228
And you are an old man and a fool!

272
00:28:14.943 --> 00:28:15.943
Yes.

273
00:28:17.112 --> 00:28:18.488
I was a fool

274
00:28:19.865 --> 00:28:21.074
to think you were ready.

275
00:28:21.575 --> 00:28:23.869
- Father...
- (Odin shouts)

276
00:28:26.288 --> 00:28:29.333
Thor odinson.

277
00:28:31.043 --> 00:28:34.046
you have betrayed
the express command of your king.

278
00:28:34.588 --> 00:28:36.965
Through your arrogance and stupidity.

279
00:28:37.049 --> 00:28:39.885
you've opened these peaceful realms
andinnocenthves

280
00:28:39.968 --> 00:28:43.847
to the horror and desolation of war!

281
00:28:49.728 --> 00:28:53.607
You are unworthy of these realms!

282
00:28:53.941 --> 00:28:56.568
You're unworthy of your title!

283
00:28:56.652 --> 00:28:58.362
You're unworthy

284
00:29:00.906 --> 00:29:04.910
of the loved ones you have betrayed.

285
00:29:15.879 --> 00:29:18.006
I now take from you your power!

286
00:29:19.007 --> 00:29:21.551
In the name of my father

287
00:29:22.177 --> 00:29:24.137
and his father before.

288
00:29:24.680 --> 00:29:27.349
I. Odin all father. cast you out!

289
00:29:34.064 --> 00:29:37.276
Whosoever holds this hammer.
if he be worthy.

290
00:29:37.359 --> 00:29:38.986
shall possess the power of Thor.

291
00:29:52.833 --> 00:29:54.167
(Darcy and Jane screaming)

292
00:30:04.136 --> 00:30:05.780
Darcy: I think that was legally your fault.

293
00:30:05.804 --> 00:30:07.556
Jane: Get the first aid kit.

294
00:30:07.639 --> 00:30:09.099
Do me a favor and don't be dead.

295
00:30:09.182 --> 00:30:10.726
(Gasps)

296
00:30:14.646 --> 00:30:17.107
Whoa. Does he need cpr?
Because I totally know cpr.

297
00:30:26.992 --> 00:30:28.327
(Groans)

298
00:30:29.995 --> 00:30:31.413
Where did he come from?

299
00:30:35.375 --> 00:30:36.376
You all right?

300
00:30:36.460 --> 00:30:37.544
Hammer?

301
00:30:37.961 --> 00:30:38.837
Hammer?

302
00:30:38.920 --> 00:30:41.089
Yeah. we can tell you're hammered.
It's pretty obvious.

303
00:30:41.423 --> 00:30:44.301
(Gasps) Oh. my god. Erik. look at this!

304
00:30:44.384 --> 00:30:47.054
We have to move quickly
before this all changes.

305
00:30:48.013 --> 00:30:49.723
Jane. we have to take him
to the hospital.

306
00:30:49.806 --> 00:30:52.225
- Father!
- Jane: He's fine. look at him.

307
00:30:52.309 --> 00:30:56.313
Heimdall! I know you can hear me!
Open the Bifrost!

308
00:30:56.396 --> 00:30:58.315
Jane: Hospital. You go. I'll stay.

309
00:30:58.398 --> 00:31:00.942
You. What realm is this?

310
00:31:01.026 --> 00:31:02.527
Alfheim? Nornheim?

311
00:31:02.611 --> 00:31:03.612
New Mexico.

312
00:31:03.862 --> 00:31:07.240
You dare threaten me. Thor.
with so puny a weapon?

313
00:31:07.324 --> 00:31:09.409
- (Fires taser gun)
- (Shuddering)

314
00:31:11.411 --> 00:31:13.497
What? He was freaking me out!

315
00:31:13.955 --> 00:31:15.999
Next time you decide to taser somebody.

316
00:31:16.083 --> 00:31:18.543
make sure he's already in the car. okay?

317
00:31:19.711 --> 00:31:21.797
Jane! Come on.

318
00:31:39.648 --> 00:31:40.857
Nurse: Name?

319
00:31:40.941 --> 00:31:43.151
He said it was Thor?

320
00:31:43.610 --> 00:31:46.822
T-h-o-r.

321
00:31:47.280 --> 00:31:49.908
- And your relationship to him?
- I've never met him before.

322
00:31:49.991 --> 00:31:51.451
Until she hit him with a car.

323
00:31:51.535 --> 00:31:54.287
I grazed him. but she tasered him.

324
00:31:54.579 --> 00:31:55.831
Yes. I did.

325
00:32:00.001 --> 00:32:01.081
Just taking a little blood.

326
00:32:01.378 --> 00:32:03.505
How dare you attack the son of Odin?

327
00:32:03.588 --> 00:32:05.382
Male nurse: I need some help!

328
00:32:06.425 --> 00:32:08.093
Call security!

329
00:32:08.343 --> 00:32:10.512
Man: Security to er 3. stat!

330
00:32:24.359 --> 00:32:26.445
You're no match for the mighty...

331
00:33:19.289 --> 00:33:20.289
Huh.

332
00:33:28.423 --> 00:33:30.823
Erik: You don't think
this was just a magnetic storm. do you?

333
00:33:30.884 --> 00:33:33.929
Look. the lensing around these edges

334
00:33:34.012 --> 00:33:36.515
is characteristic
of an Einstein-rosen bridge.

335
00:33:36.598 --> 00:33:37.641
A what?

336
00:33:37.724 --> 00:33:39.869
- I thought you were a science major.
- Political science.

337
00:33:39.893 --> 00:33:41.645
She was the only applicant.

338
00:33:41.937 --> 00:33:44.481
An Einstein-rosen bridge
is a theoretical connection

339
00:33:44.564 --> 00:33:45.875
between two different points
of space-time.

340
00:33:45.899 --> 00:33:47.275
It's a wormhole.

341
00:33:47.359 --> 00:33:50.320
- Erik. look. What do you see?
- Stars.

342
00:33:50.403 --> 00:33:52.280
Yeah. but not our stars.

343
00:33:52.364 --> 00:33:56.117
See. this is the star alignment
for our quadrant this time of year.

344
00:33:56.201 --> 00:33:59.287
and unless ursa minor decided
to take a day off.

345
00:33:59.704 --> 00:34:01.623
these are someone else's constellations.

346
00:34:01.706 --> 00:34:03.542
Hey! Check this out.

347
00:34:10.298 --> 00:34:12.092
No. it can't be.

348
00:34:14.052 --> 00:34:16.179
I think I left something at the hospital.

349
00:34:31.736 --> 00:34:33.905
It's not possible!

350
00:34:36.074 --> 00:34:38.076
(Panting)

351
00:34:47.544 --> 00:34:50.255
He was on drugs or something.
He just went nuts.

352
00:34:58.930 --> 00:35:00.599
Darcy: Oh. my god.

353
00:35:04.019 --> 00:35:06.271
I just lost
my most important piece of evidence.

354
00:35:06.354 --> 00:35:07.188
Typical.

355
00:35:07.272 --> 00:35:09.524
- So now what?
- We find him.

356
00:35:09.608 --> 00:35:10.942
Did you see what he did in there?

357
00:35:11.026 --> 00:35:12.861
I'm not sure finding him is the best idea.

358
00:35:12.944 --> 00:35:15.298
Well. our data can't tell us
what it was like to be inside that event.

359
00:35:15.322 --> 00:35:17.699
and he can. So. we're gonna find him.

360
00:35:18.283 --> 00:35:19.117
Darcy: Okay.

361
00:35:19.200 --> 00:35:21.077
So we're gonna look
all over new Mexico. right?

362
00:35:21.953 --> 00:35:23.288
Exactly.

363
00:35:23.371 --> 00:35:24.998
(Engine revs)

364
00:35:27.417 --> 00:35:28.627
Jane: What?

365
00:35:29.628 --> 00:35:32.756
I'm so sorry.
I swear I'm not doing this on purpose.

366
00:35:32.839 --> 00:35:34.633
(Upbeat music playing)

367
00:35:36.593 --> 00:35:40.597
(Chattering)

368
00:35:43.016 --> 00:35:44.392
Yeah!

369
00:35:44.476 --> 00:35:45.476
(Laughing)

370
00:35:49.856 --> 00:35:51.483
I got it. I got it.

371
00:36:01.242 --> 00:36:03.078
Man: Come on. kick it in now!

372
00:36:06.164 --> 00:36:08.291
(Engine revving)

373
00:36:10.335 --> 00:36:11.670
(All exclaiming)

374
00:36:11.753 --> 00:36:12.921
Did it work?

375
00:36:13.004 --> 00:36:14.339
(Laughing)

376
00:36:15.256 --> 00:36:17.634
(Chattering continues)

377
00:36:34.859 --> 00:36:36.903
Sir. we found it.

378
00:36:43.284 --> 00:36:47.539
You know. for a crazy homeless person.
he's pretty cut.

379
00:36:50.625 --> 00:36:52.711
Hey. sorry I tased you!

380
00:36:55.171 --> 00:36:57.173
Excuse me. excuse me!

381
00:37:04.389 --> 00:37:05.765
What is this?

382
00:37:08.810 --> 00:37:09.978
Myex

383
00:37:10.562 --> 00:37:14.566
good with patients
and bad with relationships.

384
00:37:14.649 --> 00:37:17.026
Uh. they're the only clothes I had
that would fit you.

385
00:37:17.110 --> 00:37:18.110
They will suffice.

386
00:37:19.404 --> 00:37:20.238
You're welcome.

387
00:37:20.321 --> 00:37:21.865
Thor: This mortal form has grown weak.

388
00:37:22.657 --> 00:37:23.657
I need sustenance.

389
00:37:43.344 --> 00:37:44.763
We should never have let him go.

390
00:37:45.096 --> 00:37:46.514
There was no stopping him.

391
00:37:46.598 --> 00:37:48.678
Fandral: Well. at least
he's only banished. not dead.

392
00:37:49.058 --> 00:37:50.058
Which is what we'd all be

393
00:37:50.101 --> 00:37:52.812
if that guard hadn't told Odin
where we'd gone.

394
00:37:59.360 --> 00:38:00.612
How did the guard even know?

395
00:38:01.237 --> 00:38:02.238
I told him.

396
00:38:03.990 --> 00:38:04.991
What?

397
00:38:05.074 --> 00:38:07.368
I told him to go to Odin after we'd left.

398
00:38:07.452 --> 00:38:08.971
He should be flogged for taking so long.

399
00:38:08.995 --> 00:38:10.538
We should never have
reached Jotunheim.

400
00:38:10.622 --> 00:38:11.539
You told the guard?

401
00:38:11.623 --> 00:38:13.166
I saved our lives.

402
00:38:13.792 --> 00:38:15.627
And Thor's.

403
00:38:15.710 --> 00:38:18.171
I had no idea father would banish him
for what he did.

404
00:38:19.380 --> 00:38:20.380
Loki.

405
00:38:21.216 --> 00:38:23.927
You must go to the all father
and convince him to change his mind.

406
00:38:24.010 --> 00:38:26.095
And if I do. then what?

407
00:38:26.805 --> 00:38:30.058
I love Thor more dearly than any of you.
but you know what he is.

408
00:38:30.141 --> 00:38:32.769
He's arrogant.
He's reckless. He's dangerous.

409
00:38:32.852 --> 00:38:34.813
You saw how he was today.

410
00:38:35.146 --> 00:38:36.746
Is that what asgard needs from its king?

411
00:38:41.486 --> 00:38:46.115
He may speak of the good of asgard.
but he's always been jealous of Thor.

412
00:38:47.075 --> 00:38:49.285
We should be grateful to him.
he saved our lives.

413
00:38:49.577 --> 00:38:50.995
Laufey said

414
00:38:51.579 --> 00:38:53.998
there were traitors in the house of Odin.

415
00:38:54.833 --> 00:38:58.920
A master of magic
could bring three jotuns into asgard.

416
00:39:00.713 --> 00:39:02.473
Fandral:
Loki's always been one for mischief.

417
00:39:02.507 --> 00:39:04.926
but you're talking
about something else entirely.

418
00:39:25.446 --> 00:39:26.781
Odin: Stop!

419
00:39:30.451 --> 00:39:31.953
Loki: Am I cursed?

420
00:39:32.412 --> 00:39:33.454
Odin: No.

421
00:39:37.625 --> 00:39:38.835
What am I?

422
00:39:39.961 --> 00:39:41.129
You're my son.

423
00:39:51.639 --> 00:39:53.349
What more than that?

424
00:39:58.229 --> 00:40:01.232
The casket wasn't the only thing
you took from Jotunheim that day.

425
00:40:01.316 --> 00:40:02.317
was it?

426
00:40:12.201 --> 00:40:13.304
In the aftermath of the battle.

427
00:40:13.328 --> 00:40:16.205
I went into the temple
and I found a baby.

428
00:40:16.289 --> 00:40:17.582
(Crying)

429
00:40:20.668 --> 00:40:23.504
Small for a giant's offspring.

430
00:40:24.088 --> 00:40:26.841
Abandoned. suffering. left to die.

431
00:40:28.009 --> 00:40:29.302
Laufey's son.

432
00:40:31.346 --> 00:40:33.014
Laufey's son.

433
00:40:36.768 --> 00:40:37.769
Yes.

434
00:40:41.439 --> 00:40:42.440
Why?

435
00:40:43.024 --> 00:40:46.194
You were knee-deep in jotun blood.
why would you take me?

436
00:40:46.277 --> 00:40:47.737
You were an innocent child.

437
00:40:47.820 --> 00:40:51.658
No. You took me for a purpose.
What was it?

438
00:40:55.536 --> 00:40:57.455
(Shouting) Tell me!

439
00:40:59.207 --> 00:41:02.043
I thought
we could unite our kingdoms one day.

440
00:41:02.627 --> 00:41:05.463
Bring about an alliance.
bring about permanent peace.

441
00:41:05.797 --> 00:41:06.965
Through you.

442
00:41:07.382 --> 00:41:08.508
What?

443
00:41:09.384 --> 00:41:11.636
But those plans no longer matter.

444
00:41:13.388 --> 00:41:16.474
So I am no more
than another stolen relic.

445
00:41:16.933 --> 00:41:19.143
locked up here
until you might have use of me.

446
00:41:19.227 --> 00:41:20.728
Why do you twist my words?

447
00:41:20.812 --> 00:41:22.873
You could have told me what I was
from the beginning.

448
00:41:22.897 --> 00:41:23.898
why didn't you?

449
00:41:24.273 --> 00:41:25.316
You're my son.

450
00:41:25.900 --> 00:41:28.486
I wanted only to protect you
from the truth.

451
00:41:28.569 --> 00:41:31.072
What? Because I'm the monster

452
00:41:31.155 --> 00:41:33.241
parents tell their children about at night?

453
00:41:33.741 --> 00:41:35.469
- No. no.
- You know. it all makes sense now!

454
00:41:35.493 --> 00:41:38.246
Why you favored Thor all these years!

455
00:41:38.329 --> 00:41:41.165
Because no matter how much
you claim to love me.

456
00:41:41.791 --> 00:41:44.877
you could never have a frost giant
sitting on the throne of asgard!

457
00:42:04.939 --> 00:42:06.357
Guards!

458
00:42:07.108 --> 00:42:09.068
Guards. please. help!

459
00:42:15.116 --> 00:42:16.868
Jane: How'd you get inside that cloud?

460
00:42:17.285 --> 00:42:19.620
Darcy: Also. how could you eat
an entire box of pop-tarts

461
00:42:19.704 --> 00:42:21.205
and still be this hungry?

462
00:42:27.045 --> 00:42:29.464
- This drink. I like it.
- I know. It's great. right?

463
00:42:29.547 --> 00:42:30.715
Another!

464
00:42:32.050 --> 00:42:34.177
Jane: Sorry. Izzy. Little accident.

465
00:42:37.472 --> 00:42:39.450
- What was that?
- It was delicious. I want another.

466
00:42:39.474 --> 00:42:41.476
- Well. you could have just said so.
- I just did.

467
00:42:41.559 --> 00:42:44.687
- No. I mean. ask nicely.
- I meant no disrespect.

468
00:42:44.771 --> 00:42:46.355
All right. Well. no more smashing.

469
00:42:46.939 --> 00:42:47.939
Deal?

470
00:42:50.568 --> 00:42:51.568
You have my word.

471
00:42:52.737 --> 00:42:53.738
Good.

472
00:42:55.239 --> 00:42:56.908
Man 1: The usual. please. Izzy.

473
00:42:56.991 --> 00:42:59.744
Man 2: You missed all the excitement
out at the crater.

474
00:42:59.827 --> 00:43:03.081
Man 1: They're saying some kind
of satellite landed out in the desert.

475
00:43:03.164 --> 00:43:05.541
Man 2: Yeah. we were having
a good time with it

476
00:43:05.625 --> 00:43:07.001
until the feds showed up.

477
00:43:07.085 --> 00:43:09.754
Jane: Excuse me.
Did you say there was a satellite crash?

478
00:43:09.837 --> 00:43:10.837
Man 2: Yeah.

479
00:43:11.130 --> 00:43:13.341
Oh. my god. This is going on Facebook.
Smile.

480
00:43:15.927 --> 00:43:17.678
What did it look like. the satellite?

481
00:43:17.762 --> 00:43:21.432
Well. I don't know anything
about satellites. but it was heavy.

482
00:43:22.308 --> 00:43:24.852
I mean. nobody could lift it.

483
00:43:25.937 --> 00:43:28.397
They said it was radioactive.
I had my hands all over it.

484
00:43:28.815 --> 00:43:30.316
Which way?

485
00:43:30.399 --> 00:43:32.401
Oh. uh...

486
00:43:32.485 --> 00:43:34.487
Fifty miles west of here.

487
00:43:34.987 --> 00:43:36.572
Man 1: Well. iwouldn't waste my time!

488
00:43:36.656 --> 00:43:38.656
Looked like the whole army
was coming when we left.

489
00:43:39.826 --> 00:43:41.494
- (Brakes squealing)
- (Honking)

490
00:43:43.496 --> 00:43:44.831
- Driver: Dumbass!
- (Honking)

491
00:43:45.915 --> 00:43:46.999
Where are you going?

492
00:43:47.291 --> 00:43:49.418
- Fifty miles west of here.
- Why?

493
00:43:49.502 --> 00:43:52.880
- To get what belongs to me.
- Oh. so you own a satellite now?

494
00:43:52.964 --> 00:43:54.024
It's not what they say it is.

495
00:43:54.048 --> 00:43:55.091
Well. whatever it is.

496
00:43:55.174 --> 00:43:56.568
the government seems to think it's theirs.

497
00:43:56.592 --> 00:43:58.469
So. you just intend to go in there
and take it?

498
00:43:58.553 --> 00:43:59.804
Yes.

499
00:44:01.139 --> 00:44:02.431
If you take me there now.

500
00:44:02.807 --> 00:44:04.487
I'll tell you everything you wish to know.

501
00:44:04.517 --> 00:44:05.601
- Everything?
- Yes.

502
00:44:05.685 --> 00:44:08.479
All the answers you seek will be yours
once I reclaim Mjolnir.

503
00:44:08.563 --> 00:44:10.648
Myeu-muh? What's myeu-muh?

504
00:44:10.898 --> 00:44:12.358
Can I have a word. Jane?

505
00:44:16.863 --> 00:44:18.447
Please don't do this.

506
00:44:18.698 --> 00:44:20.575
(Softly) You saw what I saw last night.

507
00:44:20.658 --> 00:44:22.970
This is no coincidence.
We have to find out what's in that crater.

508
00:44:22.994 --> 00:44:25.013
But I'm not talking about the crater.
I'm talking about him.

509
00:44:25.037 --> 00:44:27.748
- But he's promising us answers.
- He's delusional.

510
00:44:27.832 --> 00:44:28.916
Listen to what he's saying.

511
00:44:29.000 --> 00:44:32.587
He's talking about Mjolnir
and Thor and Bifrost.

512
00:44:33.379 --> 00:44:35.381
It's the stories I grew up with as a child.

513
00:44:35.464 --> 00:44:38.217
I'm just going to drive him. That's it.

514
00:44:38.718 --> 00:44:40.636
He's dangerous. Jane.

515
00:44:46.642 --> 00:44:49.395
I'm sorry. but I can't take you.

516
00:44:49.478 --> 00:44:50.980
Then this is where we say goodbye.

517
00:44:55.318 --> 00:44:56.736
(Giggles)

518
00:45:01.574 --> 00:45:03.075
Thank you?

519
00:45:03.993 --> 00:45:05.328
Jane foster.

520
00:45:05.828 --> 00:45:07.121
Erik selvig.

521
00:45:07.496 --> 00:45:08.664
Darcy.

522
00:45:09.207 --> 00:45:10.374
farewell.

523
00:45:14.170 --> 00:45:15.504
All right.

524
00:45:16.172 --> 00:45:17.757
Back to work.

525
00:45:34.106 --> 00:45:35.441
(Truck honking)

526
00:45:38.194 --> 00:45:39.779
That's my stuff!

527
00:45:44.450 --> 00:45:45.785
What the hell is going on here?

528
00:45:45.868 --> 00:45:47.708
Ms. Foster.
I'm agent Coulson with S.H.I.E.L.D.

529
00:45:47.787 --> 00:45:49.580
Is that supposed to mean something
to me?

530
00:45:49.664 --> 00:45:50.831
- You can't do this!
- Jane!

531
00:45:51.249 --> 00:45:54.043
Jane. this is a lot more serious
than you realize. Let it go.

532
00:45:54.126 --> 00:45:56.128
Let it go? This is my life.

533
00:45:56.587 --> 00:45:58.673
We're investigating a security threat.

534
00:45:58.756 --> 00:46:01.356
We need to appropriate your records
and all your atmospheric data.

535
00:46:01.384 --> 00:46:03.970
By "appropriate." do you mean steal?

536
00:46:04.053 --> 00:46:05.721
Here. this should
more than compensate you

537
00:46:05.805 --> 00:46:06.681
for your trouble.

538
00:46:06.764 --> 00:46:09.392
I can't just buy replacements
at radio shack.

539
00:46:09.475 --> 00:46:11.310
I made most of this equipment myself!

540
00:46:11.394 --> 00:46:12.754
Then I'm sure you can do it again.

541
00:46:12.812 --> 00:46:15.773
And I'm sure I can sue you
for violating my constitutional rights!

542
00:46:15.856 --> 00:46:18.401
I'm sorry. Ms. Foster.
but we're the good guys.

543
00:46:18.484 --> 00:46:20.111
So are we!

544
00:46:20.444 --> 00:46:23.823
I'm on the verge of understanding
something extraordinary.

545
00:46:23.906 --> 00:46:25.741
And everything I know
about this phenomenon

546
00:46:25.825 --> 00:46:27.827
is either in this lab or in this book.

547
00:46:27.910 --> 00:46:30.538
And you can't just take this away... hey!

548
00:46:30.955 --> 00:46:34.500
Jane! Easy! Easy. Jane...

549
00:46:36.919 --> 00:46:38.629
Thank you for your cooperation.

550
00:46:56.605 --> 00:46:57.898
Years of research.

551
00:46:58.357 --> 00:46:59.357
gone.

552
00:46:59.942 --> 00:47:01.736
Darcy: They even took my iPod.

553
00:47:02.528 --> 00:47:05.114
- Erik: What about the backups?
- Jane: They took our backups.

554
00:47:05.406 --> 00:47:08.951
They took the backups of our backups.
They were extremely thorough.

555
00:47:09.035 --> 00:47:11.370
I just downloaded. like.
30 songs onto there.

556
00:47:11.454 --> 00:47:13.956
Could you please stop with your iPod?

557
00:47:14.874 --> 00:47:16.959
Who are these people?

558
00:47:18.502 --> 00:47:20.504
I knew this scientist.

559
00:47:20.921 --> 00:47:23.507
The pioneer in gamma radiation.

560
00:47:23.591 --> 00:47:25.801
S.H.I.E.L.D. showed up and. uh...

561
00:47:27.053 --> 00:47:28.637
He wasn't heard from again.

562
00:47:29.680 --> 00:47:32.975
They're not gonna do that to us.
I'm gonna get everything back.

563
00:47:33.059 --> 00:47:35.728
Come on. please.
Let me contact one of my colleagues.

564
00:47:35.811 --> 00:47:37.855
He's had some dealings
with these people before.

565
00:47:38.522 --> 00:47:41.150
I'll e-mail him and maybe he can help.

566
00:47:41.776 --> 00:47:43.152
They took your laptop. too.

567
00:47:52.161 --> 00:47:55.331
Allfather.
we must speak with you urgently.

568
00:48:08.177 --> 00:48:10.096
My friends.

569
00:48:10.638 --> 00:48:11.806
Where's Odin?

570
00:48:12.431 --> 00:48:15.351
Father has fallen into the odinsleep.

571
00:48:16.852 --> 00:48:19.355
Mother fears
he may never awaken again.

572
00:48:20.022 --> 00:48:21.065
We would speak with her.

573
00:48:21.148 --> 00:48:24.610
She has refused to leave
my father's bedside.

574
00:48:26.862 --> 00:48:29.615
You can bring your urgent matter to me.

575
00:48:35.413 --> 00:48:36.956
(Spear thudding)

576
00:48:37.039 --> 00:48:38.374
Your king.

577
00:48:49.593 --> 00:48:53.889
My king. we would ask
that you end Thor's banishment.

578
00:48:55.057 --> 00:48:56.308
(Chuckles)

579
00:48:58.561 --> 00:49:01.897
My first command
cannot be to undo the all father's last.

580
00:49:04.733 --> 00:49:07.278
We're on the brink of war
with Jotunheim.

581
00:49:08.446 --> 00:49:11.157
Our people need a sense of continuity.

582
00:49:11.240 --> 00:49:14.076
in order to feel safe
in these difficult times.

583
00:49:15.411 --> 00:49:16.954
All of us must stand together

584
00:49:17.997 --> 00:49:19.623
for the good of asgard.

585
00:49:22.168 --> 00:49:23.669
Yes. of course.

586
00:49:23.919 --> 00:49:26.839
- Good. Then you will wait for my word.
- Ifl may...

587
00:49:28.507 --> 00:49:33.095
Beg the indulgence of your majesty
to perhaps reconsider...

588
00:49:33.179 --> 00:49:34.472
We're done!

589
00:50:25.064 --> 00:50:26.148
(Scoffs)

590
00:50:26.232 --> 00:50:28.234
(Engine idling)

591
00:50:38.369 --> 00:50:39.370
I need a horse!

592
00:50:41.747 --> 00:50:44.792
We don't have horses.
Just dogs. cats. birds...

593
00:50:44.875 --> 00:50:46.752
Then give me one of those
large enough to ride.

594
00:50:46.835 --> 00:50:49.797
- (Honking)
- Hey. you still need a lift?

595
00:50:54.718 --> 00:50:57.388
I've never done anything like this before.

596
00:50:58.681 --> 00:51:01.475
Have you ever done
anything like this before?

597
00:51:02.226 --> 00:51:03.727
Many times.

598
00:51:04.520 --> 00:51:05.854
But you're brave to do it.

599
00:51:06.146 --> 00:51:08.232
Well. they just stole my entire life's work.

600
00:51:08.607 --> 00:51:10.693
I don't really have much left to lose.

601
00:51:12.069 --> 00:51:12.903
Yeah. but you're clever.

602
00:51:12.987 --> 00:51:14.029
Hmm. thanks.

603
00:51:14.113 --> 00:51:16.824
Far more clever than anyone else
in this realm.

604
00:51:17.283 --> 00:51:19.535
"Realm"? "Realm"?

605
00:51:20.119 --> 00:51:22.871
- You think me strange.
- Yeah. I do.

606
00:51:23.414 --> 00:51:25.541
Good strange or bad strange?

607
00:51:26.000 --> 00:51:27.543
I'm not quite sure yet.

608
00:51:28.043 --> 00:51:29.420
(Tires screeching)

609
00:51:30.337 --> 00:51:32.256
(Both laughing)

610
00:51:32.923 --> 00:51:34.592
I'm sorry.

611
00:51:39.722 --> 00:51:40.722
But who are you?

612
00:51:43.100 --> 00:51:44.435
Really?

613
00:51:46.979 --> 00:51:48.272
You'll see soon enough.

614
00:51:49.315 --> 00:51:50.774
You promised me answers.

615
00:51:54.486 --> 00:51:56.196
What you seek. it's a bridge.

616
00:51:56.655 --> 00:51:58.490
Like an Einstein-rosen bridge?

617
00:51:58.574 --> 00:51:59.783
More like a rainbow bridge.

618
00:52:03.120 --> 00:52:04.830
God. I hope you're not crazy.

619
00:52:15.132 --> 00:52:17.509
Loki: (Softly)
I never get used to seeing him like this.

620
00:52:18.177 --> 00:52:22.473
Frigga: He's put it off for so long now.
that I fear...

621
00:52:24.975 --> 00:52:26.393
How long will it last?

622
00:52:27.144 --> 00:52:31.273
I don't know. This time it's different.
We were unprepared.

623
00:52:33.651 --> 00:52:35.069
So why did he lie?

624
00:52:36.153 --> 00:52:40.074
He kept the truth from you
so that you would never feel different.

625
00:52:40.491 --> 00:52:42.826
You are our son. loki.

626
00:52:43.327 --> 00:52:45.454
and we. your family.

627
00:52:47.081 --> 00:52:51.335
We mustn't lose hope
that your father will return to us.

628
00:52:52.503 --> 00:52:53.921
And your brother.

629
00:52:55.381 --> 00:52:57.216
What hope is there for Thor?

630
00:52:57.508 --> 00:53:00.969
There's always a purpose
to everything your father does.

631
00:53:28.747 --> 00:53:30.374
(Thunder crashing)

632
00:53:33.836 --> 00:53:35.421
Jane: That's no satellite crash!

633
00:53:35.504 --> 00:53:36.856
They would have hauled
the wreckage away.

634
00:53:36.880 --> 00:53:38.560
they wouldn't have built a city around it.

635
00:53:39.883 --> 00:53:43.345
- You're going to need this.
- What? Wait. why?

636
00:53:43.429 --> 00:53:45.055
(Thunder rumbling)

637
00:53:46.724 --> 00:53:48.058
Now stay here.

638
00:53:48.308 --> 00:53:51.562
Once I have Mjolnir. I will return
the items they've stolen from you.

639
00:53:52.271 --> 00:53:53.271
Deal?

640
00:53:53.522 --> 00:53:55.983
No. Look what's down there.

641
00:53:56.066 --> 00:53:58.944
You think you're just gonna walk in.
grab our stuff and walk out?

642
00:53:59.027 --> 00:54:00.946
No. I'm going to fly out.

643
00:54:08.996 --> 00:54:11.996
Technician: Sir. feed from the keyhole
can barely penetrate the cloud cover.

644
00:54:12.040 --> 00:54:13.226
Tech's barely working as it is.

645
00:54:13.250 --> 00:54:15.377
with all the interference
that thing's giving off.

646
00:54:16.086 --> 00:54:18.505
And we've got a commercial aircraft
coming right over us.

647
00:54:18.589 --> 00:54:21.675
Southwest airlines. flight 5434.

648
00:54:21.759 --> 00:54:22.999
Reroute it like all the others.

649
00:54:24.261 --> 00:54:25.261
Hold a sec.

650
00:54:25.304 --> 00:54:28.056
We've got something outside the fence.
West Side.

651
00:54:28.140 --> 00:54:31.727
Agent: Delancey. Jackson.
West Side perimeter. Go check it out.

652
00:54:34.229 --> 00:54:35.230
There it is.

653
00:54:44.323 --> 00:54:45.824
Delancey. Jackson. Report.

654
00:54:54.291 --> 00:54:56.126
Agent down.
We've got a perimeter breach.

655
00:54:57.127 --> 00:54:59.129
(Klaxons blaring)

656
00:55:02.716 --> 00:55:03.926
(Gasps)

657
00:55:09.181 --> 00:55:13.310
You've reached Dr. Erik selvig.
please leave me a message.

658
00:55:14.102 --> 00:55:16.730
Hi. Erik. it's me.
Don't worry. I'm fine. but...

659
00:55:17.648 --> 00:55:20.025
Just in case
you don't hear from me in the next hour.

660
00:55:20.400 --> 00:55:22.820
just come by the crater site
and try and find me. okay?

661
00:55:22.903 --> 00:55:25.614
I did exactly what you told me not to.
I'm sorry.

662
00:55:26.156 --> 00:55:27.658
So sorry. Bye.

663
00:55:31.495 --> 00:55:32.695
Agent 1: Bravo quadrant. move!

664
00:55:33.747 --> 00:55:35.123
(Thunder crashing)

665
00:55:35.207 --> 00:55:37.292
(High-pitched hum)

666
00:55:46.176 --> 00:55:48.136
Agent 2: Entering south tunnel!

667
00:55:49.555 --> 00:55:51.315
Agent 3: Negative. negative.
I have no comms.

668
00:56:04.987 --> 00:56:06.989
Agent 4: Target sighted. east tunnel!

669
00:56:07.239 --> 00:56:08.824
I need eyes up high. with a gun.

670
00:56:34.683 --> 00:56:35.976
Moving north!

671
00:56:43.901 --> 00:56:44.776
What have we got?

672
00:56:44.860 --> 00:56:46.420
There's a massive electromagnetic surge

673
00:56:46.486 --> 00:56:47.362
coming off that thing.

674
00:56:47.446 --> 00:56:49.364
Systems are barely coping.

675
00:56:49.698 --> 00:56:51.408
Barton? Talk to me.

676
00:56:52.868 --> 00:56:54.453
You want me to slow him down. sir?

677
00:56:55.704 --> 00:56:57.831
Or are you sending in more guys
for him to beat up?

678
00:56:58.165 --> 00:56:59.625
I'll let you know.

679
00:57:14.473 --> 00:57:15.807
You're big.

680
00:57:16.934 --> 00:57:18.310
Fought bigger.

681
00:58:02.604 --> 00:58:06.191
Better call it. Coulson.
'cause I'm starting to root for this guy.

682
00:58:27.254 --> 00:58:28.254
Last chance. sir.

683
00:58:28.296 --> 00:58:30.257
Coulson: Wait. I want to see this.

684
00:58:40.851 --> 00:58:41.852
(Grunting)

685
00:59:13.550 --> 00:59:15.469
(Screaming)

686
00:59:39.534 --> 00:59:41.828
All right. show's over.
Ground units. move in.

687
01:00:35.173 --> 01:00:37.050
Erik: He committed a crime. He's in jail!

688
01:00:37.134 --> 01:00:39.427
Jane: I can't just leave him there!
Erik: Why?

689
01:00:39.511 --> 01:00:41.721
You didn't see what I saw!

690
01:00:41.972 --> 01:00:44.015
Darcy: (Gasps) Look!
Look. it's myeu-muh.

691
01:00:48.645 --> 01:00:49.855
Where'd you find this?

692
01:00:49.938 --> 01:00:51.273
Erik: The children's section.

693
01:00:51.356 --> 01:00:53.608
I just wanted to show you
how silly his story was.

694
01:00:53.692 --> 01:00:55.777
But you're the one
who's always pushing me

695
01:00:55.861 --> 01:00:58.029
to chase down every possibility.
every alternative!

696
01:00:58.113 --> 01:01:00.157
I'm talking about science. not magic!

697
01:01:00.240 --> 01:01:02.701
Well. magic's just science
that we don't understand yet.

698
01:01:02.784 --> 01:01:05.162
- Arthur c. Clarke.
- Who wrote science fiction.

699
01:01:05.245 --> 01:01:07.956
- A precursor to science fact!
- In some cases. yeah.

700
01:01:08.039 --> 01:01:09.642
Well. if there is an Einstein-rosen bridge.

701
01:01:09.666 --> 01:01:11.269
then there's something on the other side.

702
01:01:11.293 --> 01:01:12.895
And advanced beings
could have crossed it!

703
01:01:12.919 --> 01:01:14.004
Oh. Jane.

704
01:01:14.087 --> 01:01:17.090
A primitive culture like the vikings
might have worshipped them as deities.

705
01:01:17.174 --> 01:01:18.925
Yes! Yes. exactly. Thank you.

706
01:01:19.009 --> 01:01:20.635
Darcy: Mmm-hmm.

707
01:01:23.054 --> 01:01:24.222
(Sighs)

708
01:01:26.850 --> 01:01:27.976
Coulson: You made my men.

709
01:01:28.059 --> 01:01:30.562
some of the most
highly trained professionals in the world.

710
01:01:30.645 --> 01:01:33.398
look like a bunch of minimum-wage
mall cops.

711
01:01:35.233 --> 01:01:36.359
That's hurtful.

712
01:01:37.569 --> 01:01:41.031
In my experience. it takes someone
who's received similar training

713
01:01:41.489 --> 01:01:42.741
to do what you did to them.

714
01:01:44.201 --> 01:01:46.703
Why don't you tell me
where you received your training?

715
01:01:46.953 --> 01:01:50.373
Pakistan? Chechnya? Afghanistan?

716
01:01:51.708 --> 01:01:54.753
No. you strike me
more as the soldier of fortune type.

717
01:01:55.879 --> 01:01:58.840
Where was it? South Africa?

718
01:02:00.342 --> 01:02:04.262
Certain groups pay very well
for a good mercenary like you.

719
01:02:06.598 --> 01:02:07.766
Who are you?

720
01:02:12.938 --> 01:02:15.398
One way or another.
we find out what we need to know.

721
01:02:15.774 --> 01:02:16.900
We're good at that.

722
01:02:17.442 --> 01:02:19.110
(Pager beeping)

723
01:02:22.781 --> 01:02:23.865
Don't go anywhere.

724
01:02:30.622 --> 01:02:33.124
Loki! What are you doing here?

725
01:02:33.416 --> 01:02:34.626
I had to see you.

726
01:02:36.628 --> 01:02:37.963
What's happened?

727
01:02:38.296 --> 01:02:40.298
Tell me. Is it Jotunheim?

728
01:02:40.632 --> 01:02:41.841
Let me explain to father.

729
01:02:41.925 --> 01:02:43.385
Father is dead.

730
01:02:49.641 --> 01:02:50.892
What?

731
01:02:52.811 --> 01:02:54.396
Your banishment.

732
01:02:55.397 --> 01:02:57.649
the threat of a new war.

733
01:02:58.608 --> 01:03:00.277
it was too much for him to bear.

734
01:03:03.154 --> 01:03:04.948
You mustn't blame yourself.

735
01:03:06.032 --> 01:03:07.826
I know that you loved him.

736
01:03:08.451 --> 01:03:10.829
I tried to tell him so.
but he wouldn't listen.

737
01:03:13.581 --> 01:03:15.667
It was so cruel
to put the hammer within your reach.

738
01:03:15.750 --> 01:03:17.836
knowing that you could never lift it.

739
01:03:21.172 --> 01:03:23.300
The burden of the throne
has fallen to me now.

740
01:03:30.015 --> 01:03:31.766
Can I come home?

741
01:03:32.642 --> 01:03:35.645
The truce with Jotunheim
is conditional upon your exile.

742
01:03:35.979 --> 01:03:41.735
- Yes. but couldn't we find a way...
- And mother has forbidden your return.

743
01:03:45.238 --> 01:03:47.032
This is goodbye. brother.

744
01:03:49.492 --> 01:03:51.161
I'm so sorry.

745
01:03:59.669 --> 01:04:01.338
I am sorry.

746
01:04:06.718 --> 01:04:09.012
Thank you for coming here.

747
01:04:13.516 --> 01:04:14.851
Farewell.

748
01:04:27.739 --> 01:04:29.199
Good bye.

749
01:04:29.991 --> 01:04:31.034
Good bye?

750
01:04:31.743 --> 01:04:33.036
I just got back.

751
01:04:37.999 --> 01:04:39.918
(Static crackling)

752
01:04:45.924 --> 01:04:47.926
(Mjolnir humming)

753
01:05:09.072 --> 01:05:10.073
Sir?

754
01:05:11.032 --> 01:05:12.242
He's got a visitor.

755
01:05:17.580 --> 01:05:19.332
His name is Donald Blake?

756
01:05:19.749 --> 01:05:21.334
Dr. Donald Blake.

757
01:05:21.418 --> 01:05:23.378
You have dangerous coworkers.
Dr. Selvig.

758
01:05:23.711 --> 01:05:27.257
He was distraught when he found out
that you've taken all of our research.

759
01:05:28.091 --> 01:05:30.593
That was years of his life. gone!

760
01:05:32.554 --> 01:05:34.764
You can understand
how a man could go off like that.

761
01:05:35.265 --> 01:05:37.392
A big. faceless organization like yours

762
01:05:37.475 --> 01:05:39.352
coming in with their
jackbooted thugs and...

763
01:05:41.604 --> 01:05:42.897
That's how he put it.

764
01:05:42.981 --> 01:05:44.023
That still doesn't explain

765
01:05:44.107 --> 01:05:45.827
how he managed
to tear through our security.

766
01:05:46.276 --> 01:05:49.571
Steroids! He's a bit of a fitness nut.

767
01:05:49.654 --> 01:05:51.030
(Alarm beeps)

768
01:05:51.114 --> 01:05:52.282
Technician: Sir?

769
01:05:57.120 --> 01:05:58.371
It says here that he's an md.

770
01:05:58.663 --> 01:06:00.999
Well. he is! Or he was.

771
01:06:01.082 --> 01:06:03.585
He switched careers
and became a physicist.

772
01:06:04.127 --> 01:06:05.295
A brilliant physicist.

773
01:06:05.378 --> 01:06:07.797
He's a wonderful man.
He's a man in pain.

774
01:06:10.467 --> 01:06:13.094
Erik: Oh. Donny. Donny. Donny!

775
01:06:13.678 --> 01:06:17.640
There you are. It's gonna be all right.
I'm taking you home now.

776
01:06:32.155 --> 01:06:33.656
Coulson: Dr. Selvig!

777
01:06:34.699 --> 01:06:37.160
Just keep him away from the bars.

778
01:06:37.660 --> 01:06:38.995
I will!

779
01:06:40.830 --> 01:06:43.416
- Where are we going?
- To get a drink.

780
01:06:44.000 --> 01:06:45.251
Follow them.

781
01:06:51.799 --> 01:06:53.968
You know. I had it all backwards.

782
01:06:56.012 --> 01:06:57.388
I had it all wrong.

783
01:07:00.892 --> 01:07:04.562
It's not a bad thing finding out
that you don't have all the answers.

784
01:07:05.021 --> 01:07:06.731
You start asking the right questions.

785
01:07:11.027 --> 01:07:14.989
For the first time in my life.

786
01:07:15.073 --> 01:07:19.744
I have no idea what I'm supposed to do.

787
01:07:20.745 --> 01:07:23.456
Anyone who's ever going to
find his way in this world

788
01:07:23.706 --> 01:07:26.793
has to start by admitting
he doesn't know where the hell he is.

789
01:07:28.878 --> 01:07:30.296
Thank you for what you've done.

790
01:07:30.380 --> 01:07:32.882
No. don't thank me. I only did it for Jane.

791
01:07:34.551 --> 01:07:37.220
Her father and I
taught at university together.

792
01:07:37.554 --> 01:07:39.180
He was a good man.

793
01:07:40.181 --> 01:07:41.181
He never listened.

794
01:07:42.559 --> 01:07:44.185
Neither did I.

795
01:07:45.395 --> 01:07:47.480
My father
was trying to teach me something.

796
01:07:47.564 --> 01:07:49.440
but I was too stupid to see it.

797
01:07:50.567 --> 01:07:54.612
I don't know if you're delusional
or if you're pulling some kind of con.

798
01:07:54.696 --> 01:07:55.822
and I don't care.

799
01:07:56.155 --> 01:07:57.282
I just care about her.

800
01:07:58.783 --> 01:08:00.910
I've seen the way she looks at you.

801
01:08:04.581 --> 01:08:06.916
I swear to you. I mean her no harm.

802
01:08:07.417 --> 01:08:08.418
Good.

803
01:08:09.085 --> 01:08:12.964
In that case. I'll buy you another round.
and you leave town tonight.

804
01:08:18.261 --> 01:08:20.054
Two boilermakers.

805
01:09:11.689 --> 01:09:12.940
Laufey: Kill him.

806
01:09:14.776 --> 01:09:16.736
After all I've done for you?

807
01:09:19.197 --> 01:09:23.785
So you're the one
who showed us the way into asgard.

808
01:09:24.202 --> 01:09:26.371
That was just a bit of fun. really.

809
01:09:27.538 --> 01:09:30.541
To ruin my brother's big day.

810
01:09:31.417 --> 01:09:35.171
And to protect the realm
from his idiotic rule for a while longer.

811
01:09:36.506 --> 01:09:38.841
I will hear you.

812
01:09:42.220 --> 01:09:46.641
I will conceal you
and a handful of your soldiers.

813
01:09:47.392 --> 01:09:52.397
lead you into Odin's chambers.
and you can slay him where he lies.

814
01:09:52.814 --> 01:09:54.399
Why not kill him yourself?

815
01:09:54.732 --> 01:09:55.900
(Snorts)

816
01:09:56.484 --> 01:09:59.278
I suspect that the asgardians
would not take kindly

817
01:09:59.362 --> 01:10:01.572
to a king who had murdered
his predecessor.

818
01:10:02.824 --> 01:10:05.702
Once Odin is dead.
I will return the casket to you

819
01:10:07.912 --> 01:10:10.915
and you can return Jotunheim to all its...

820
01:10:13.751 --> 01:10:15.002
Glory.

821
01:10:19.382 --> 01:10:20.800
Accept.

822
01:10:26.931 --> 01:10:28.474
What troubles you. gatekeeper?

823
01:10:28.766 --> 01:10:33.771
I turned my gaze upon you in Jotunheim.
but could neither see you nor hear you.

824
01:10:34.439 --> 01:10:35.690
You were shrouded from me.

825
01:10:35.773 --> 01:10:37.900
like the frost giants
that entered this realm.

826
01:10:38.276 --> 01:10:41.654
Perhaps your senses have weakened
after your many years of service.

827
01:10:41.738 --> 01:10:43.364
Or perhaps someone has found a way

828
01:10:43.448 --> 01:10:46.492
to hide that
which he does not wish me to see.

829
01:10:47.785 --> 01:10:49.829
You have great power. Heimdall.

830
01:10:52.415 --> 01:10:53.833
Did Odin ever fear you?

831
01:10:56.127 --> 01:10:57.795
- No.
- And why is that?

832
01:10:58.087 --> 01:11:01.090
Because he is my king
and I am sworn to obey him.

833
01:11:01.466 --> 01:11:05.636
He was your king
and you're sworn to obey me now.

834
01:11:06.637 --> 01:11:07.637
Yes?

835
01:11:12.894 --> 01:11:13.894
Yes.

836
01:11:15.104 --> 01:11:17.690
Then you will open the Bifrost to no one

837
01:11:17.940 --> 01:11:20.777
until I have repaired the damage
that my brother has done.

838
01:11:27.241 --> 01:11:28.993
(Banging on door)

839
01:11:35.374 --> 01:11:37.502
(Gasps) Oh. my god. Is he okay?

840
01:11:37.835 --> 01:11:39.629
He's fine. Not injured at all.

841
01:11:40.797 --> 01:11:42.298
- (Groans)
- I'm sorry. my friend.

842
01:11:42.381 --> 01:11:44.217
- What happened?
- We drank. we fought.

843
01:11:44.300 --> 01:11:45.802
he made his ancestors proud.

844
01:11:45.885 --> 01:11:48.095
Ah. put him on the bed.

845
01:11:53.518 --> 01:11:54.852
(Groans)

846
01:11:55.895 --> 01:11:57.438
Okay. (Laughing)

847
01:11:59.148 --> 01:12:02.610
I still don't think
you're the god of thunder.

848
01:12:03.528 --> 01:12:05.696
But you ought to be.

849
01:12:16.833 --> 01:12:18.209
Are these your chambers?

850
01:12:18.709 --> 01:12:22.046
Uh. it's more
of a temporary living situation.

851
01:12:23.214 --> 01:12:27.134
I'm sorry. I don't usually have guests.

852
01:12:27.760 --> 01:12:30.596
Actually. um. I never have guests.

853
01:12:32.723 --> 01:12:34.976
That's not the right place for it.

854
01:12:35.977 --> 01:12:37.603
I'm sorry. um...

855
01:12:40.606 --> 01:12:41.649
Can we go outside?

856
01:12:42.567 --> 01:12:43.943
Yes. of course.

857
01:12:49.532 --> 01:12:51.742
I come up here sometimes
when I can't sleep

858
01:12:51.826 --> 01:12:55.872
or I'm trying to reconcile particle data.
or when Darcy's driving me crazy.

859
01:12:57.164 --> 01:13:00.585
I come up here a lot. actually.
now that I think about it.

860
01:13:04.589 --> 01:13:06.549
I'm really glad you're safe.

861
01:13:07.633 --> 01:13:10.177
You've been very kind to me.

862
01:13:10.636 --> 01:13:12.847
and I've been far less grateful
than you deserve.

863
01:13:13.222 --> 01:13:14.902
Well. I hit you with my car
a couple times.

864
01:13:14.932 --> 01:13:17.059
so I think that kind of evens things out.

865
01:13:19.437 --> 01:13:21.147
Perhaps I had it coming.

866
01:13:27.194 --> 01:13:28.529
Oh. my god!

867
01:13:29.739 --> 01:13:31.073
I don't believe it!

868
01:13:31.282 --> 01:13:34.702
It was all I could get back.
I'm sorry it's not as much as I promised.

869
01:13:34.785 --> 01:13:39.457
No. no. this is great! This is...
I don't have to start from scratch now.

870
01:13:39.790 --> 01:13:41.208
Thank you.

871
01:13:45.796 --> 01:13:47.173
What's wrong?

872
01:13:48.674 --> 01:13:49.508
S.H.I.E.L.D.

873
01:13:49.592 --> 01:13:50.968
Whatever they are.

874
01:13:52.595 --> 01:13:54.031
they're gonna do
everything in their power

875
01:13:54.055 --> 01:13:56.849
to make sure this research
never sees the light of day.

876
01:13:56.933 --> 01:13:58.476
No. Jane.

877
01:13:59.101 --> 01:14:00.853
Listen to me. You must not give up.

878
01:14:01.270 --> 01:14:03.397
- You must finish what you've started.
- Why?

879
01:14:03.481 --> 01:14:04.899
Because you're right.

880
01:14:05.608 --> 01:14:06.943
Here. look.

881
01:14:09.487 --> 01:14:12.990
Your ancestors called it magic.
and you call it science.

882
01:14:13.616 --> 01:14:16.160
Well. I come from a place
where they're one and the same thing.

883
01:14:30.967 --> 01:14:32.510
What is that?

884
01:14:33.511 --> 01:14:36.681
My father explained it to me like this.

885
01:14:37.056 --> 01:14:38.516
that your world

886
01:14:38.599 --> 01:14:41.435
is one of the nine realms of the cosmos.

887
01:14:41.519 --> 01:14:44.397
linked to each other
by the branches of yggdrasil.

888
01:14:44.480 --> 01:14:46.065
the worlds tree.

889
01:14:47.024 --> 01:14:49.735
Now you see it every day
without realizing.

890
01:14:50.111 --> 01:14:53.030
The images glimpsed through. uh.
what did you call it? This...

891
01:14:53.531 --> 01:14:55.241
This hooble telescope.

892
01:14:55.866 --> 01:14:58.369
- Hubble.
- Hubble telescope.

893
01:14:58.452 --> 01:14:59.452
(Laughs)

894
01:15:01.831 --> 01:15:03.165
Tell me more.

895
01:15:03.708 --> 01:15:05.209
So. the nine realms.

896
01:15:05.876 --> 01:15:08.462
Now. there is midgard. which is earth.

897
01:15:08.713 --> 01:15:10.214
This is alfheim.

898
01:15:10.548 --> 01:15:13.217
Vanaheim. Jotunheim.

899
01:15:14.051 --> 01:15:15.469
And asgard.

900
01:15:15.928 --> 01:15:17.847
And that's where I come from.

901
01:15:35.239 --> 01:15:36.657
Thank you. Jane.

902
01:15:40.036 --> 01:15:42.997
Fandral: Our dearest friend banished.
loki on the throne.

903
01:15:43.080 --> 01:15:46.292
asgard on the brink of war.
yet you've managed to consume

904
01:15:46.375 --> 01:15:49.670
four wild boar.
six pheasant. a side of beef.

905
01:15:49.754 --> 01:15:53.132
and two casks of ale. Shame on you.
Don't you care?

906
01:15:54.050 --> 01:15:56.177
Do not mistake my appetite for apathy!

907
01:15:56.385 --> 01:15:58.220
Stop it. both of you!

908
01:15:58.554 --> 01:15:59.554
Stop.

909
01:16:00.723 --> 01:16:03.225
- We all know what we have to do.
- We must go.

910
01:16:05.728 --> 01:16:07.730
We must find Thor.

911
01:16:09.398 --> 01:16:10.398
It's treason.

912
01:16:10.608 --> 01:16:12.276
To hell with treason. it's suicide.

913
01:16:12.693 --> 01:16:14.570
Thor would do the same for us.

914
01:16:15.738 --> 01:16:17.073
Now shush.

915
01:16:18.616 --> 01:16:20.785
Heimdall might be watching.

916
01:16:20.868 --> 01:16:21.911
(Doors opening)

917
01:16:26.082 --> 01:16:28.584
Heimdall demands your presence.

918
01:16:33.089 --> 01:16:34.423
Volstagg: We're doomed.

919
01:16:34.507 --> 01:16:38.094
You would defy the commands of loki.
our king.

920
01:16:38.761 --> 01:16:41.222
break every oath you
have taken as warriors.

921
01:16:41.305 --> 01:16:43.724
and commit treason to bring Thor back?

922
01:16:44.016 --> 01:16:45.309
- Yes.
- Good.

923
01:16:46.268 --> 01:16:47.269
So you'll help us?

924
01:16:47.353 --> 01:16:51.649
I am bound by honor to our king.
I cannot open the bridge to you.

925
01:16:52.858 --> 01:16:54.360
Complicated fellow. isn't he?

926
01:16:54.610 --> 01:16:56.278
Now what do we do?

927
01:16:57.571 --> 01:16:58.948
Look!

928
01:17:18.342 --> 01:17:19.736
- What the hell was that?
- I don't know. sir.

929
01:17:19.760 --> 01:17:21.113
We got massive energy readings
out of nowhere

930
01:17:21.137 --> 01:17:23.597
and then they just disappeared.
Fifteen miles due northwest.

931
01:17:23.681 --> 01:17:25.015
Coulson: Let's go take a look.

932
01:17:50.040 --> 01:17:51.292
Thank you.

933
01:17:51.375 --> 01:17:53.335
- Thank you.
- You're very welcome.

934
01:18:00.467 --> 01:18:03.095
Agent: Base to team 2.
we've got activity outside the town.

935
01:18:03.179 --> 01:18:04.305
Stay on your target.

936
01:18:10.060 --> 01:18:11.145
(Spear thudding)

937
01:18:13.898 --> 01:18:16.150
Ensure my brother does not return.

938
01:18:20.070 --> 01:18:21.530
Destroy everything.

939
01:18:32.750 --> 01:18:34.084
Mom?

940
01:18:41.926 --> 01:18:43.969
Is there a renaissance fair in town?

941
01:18:44.053 --> 01:18:45.387
Call it in.

942
01:18:45.888 --> 01:18:46.889
Yeah.

943
01:18:49.099 --> 01:18:52.353
Base. we've got xena. Jackie chan
and Robin hood.

944
01:18:53.103 --> 01:18:55.397
It's a beautiful theory. Jane.

945
01:18:56.106 --> 01:18:59.360
But you won't be able to convince
the scientific community of any of it.

946
01:18:59.443 --> 01:19:00.694
Not without hard evidence.

947
01:19:01.737 --> 01:19:02.737
Found you!

948
01:19:09.078 --> 01:19:10.746
Thor: My friends!

949
01:19:12.206 --> 01:19:14.291
This is good! This is good.

950
01:19:14.625 --> 01:19:15.751
I don't believe it.

951
01:19:15.960 --> 01:19:19.004
Oh. excuse me.
Lady sif and the warriors three.

952
01:19:21.715 --> 01:19:23.175
My friends.

953
01:19:23.259 --> 01:19:25.678
I've never been happier to see anyone.

954
01:19:26.178 --> 01:19:27.680
But you should not have come.

955
01:19:29.807 --> 01:19:31.058
We're here to take you home.

956
01:19:32.518 --> 01:19:34.228
You know I can't go home.

957
01:19:36.522 --> 01:19:38.023
My father is...

958
01:19:39.149 --> 01:19:40.526
Dead because of me.

959
01:19:41.235 --> 01:19:42.736
I must remain in exile.

960
01:19:43.445 --> 01:19:44.738
Thor.

961
01:19:45.114 --> 01:19:46.865
your father still lives.

962
01:20:02.006 --> 01:20:04.925
Tell me. loki.
how did you get the jotuns into asgard?

963
01:20:05.634 --> 01:20:08.887
You think the Bifrost is the only way
in and out of this realm?

964
01:20:08.971 --> 01:20:10.448
There are secret paths
between the worlds

965
01:20:10.472 --> 01:20:12.975
to which even you. with all your gifts.
are blind.

966
01:20:13.058 --> 01:20:16.312
But I have need of them no longer.
now that I am king.

967
01:20:16.395 --> 01:20:18.063
And I say. for your act of treason.

968
01:20:18.147 --> 01:20:21.108
you are relieved of your duties
as gatekeeper.

969
01:20:21.191 --> 01:20:23.068
and no longer citizen of asgard.

970
01:20:23.652 --> 01:20:26.071
Then I need no longer obey you.

971
01:20:46.800 --> 01:20:48.719
Get somebody from linguistics
down here.

972
01:20:53.223 --> 01:20:54.808
(Thunder crashing)

973
01:20:59.730 --> 01:21:01.648
(People murmuring)

974
01:21:13.535 --> 01:21:15.162
(People exclaiming)

975
01:21:16.789 --> 01:21:18.332
Was somebody else coming?

976
01:21:22.544 --> 01:21:23.962
Is that one of stark's?

977
01:21:24.046 --> 01:21:27.591
I don't know.
The guy never tells me anything.

978
01:21:31.387 --> 01:21:32.554
Hello.

979
01:21:32.638 --> 01:21:35.349
You are using
unregistered weapons technology.

980
01:21:35.432 --> 01:21:36.517
Identify yourself.

981
01:21:40.396 --> 01:21:41.397
Here we go.

982
01:21:44.900 --> 01:21:46.110
Incoming!

983
01:21:53.742 --> 01:21:55.160
Jane. you have to leave.

984
01:21:55.244 --> 01:21:57.246
- What are you gonna do?
- I'm staying here.

985
01:21:57.538 --> 01:21:59.206
Thor's going to fight with us!

986
01:21:59.581 --> 01:22:00.916
My friends.

987
01:22:01.500 --> 01:22:05.337
I'm just a man. I'll only be in the way.
or worse. get one of you killed.

988
01:22:05.421 --> 01:22:07.464
But I can help get these people to safety.

989
01:22:07.756 --> 01:22:09.800
Well. if you're staying. then so am I.

990
01:22:10.384 --> 01:22:12.344
- We'll need some time.
- You'll have it!

991
01:22:13.053 --> 01:22:14.513
Okay. move it. people!

992
01:22:15.431 --> 01:22:17.599
Everybody out! Use the back door.

993
01:22:18.058 --> 01:22:19.351
Go. hurry! You can eat later.

994
01:22:32.197 --> 01:22:34.158
Keep it distracted.

995
01:22:48.839 --> 01:22:51.300
For asgard!

996
01:23:26.668 --> 01:23:27.668
Sif: Fall back!

997
01:23:44.061 --> 01:23:45.312
Go. Now. Run!

998
01:23:57.491 --> 01:23:58.492
(Screaming)

999
01:24:13.674 --> 01:24:16.176
Sif. Sif. you've done all you can.

1000
01:24:16.260 --> 01:24:18.554
No. I will die a warrior's death.

1001
01:24:18.762 --> 01:24:20.764
Stories will be told of this day.

1002
01:24:21.014 --> 01:24:23.892
Live. and tell those stories yourself.

1003
01:24:26.520 --> 01:24:27.938
Now go.

1004
01:24:35.571 --> 01:24:38.532
You must return to asgard.
You have to stop loki.

1005
01:24:38.782 --> 01:24:40.200
What about you?

1006
01:24:40.284 --> 01:24:42.578
Do not worry. my friends. I have a plan.

1007
01:24:43.495 --> 01:24:44.538
Come on.

1008
01:24:48.750 --> 01:24:51.044
We need to fall back. Come on.

1009
01:24:51.128 --> 01:24:52.128
Sif: Come on.

1010
01:24:59.928 --> 01:25:01.221
Wait!

1011
01:25:09.021 --> 01:25:10.230
What's he doing?

1012
01:25:37.007 --> 01:25:40.510
Brother.
whatever I have done to wrong you.

1013
01:25:41.053 --> 01:25:43.847
whatever I have done
to lead you to do this.

1014
01:25:44.514 --> 01:25:46.266
I am truly sorry.

1015
01:25:47.017 --> 01:25:49.227
But these people are innocent.

1016
01:25:50.562 --> 01:25:53.690
Taking their lives will gain you nothing.

1017
01:26:01.239 --> 01:26:02.699
So take mine

1018
01:26:03.742 --> 01:26:04.785
and end this.

1019
01:26:28.767 --> 01:26:29.767
(Gasps)

1020
01:26:36.233 --> 01:26:37.442
It's over.

1021
01:26:37.818 --> 01:26:39.945
No. It's not over.

1022
01:26:40.821 --> 01:26:42.656
I mean. you're safe.

1023
01:26:42.739 --> 01:26:44.574
We're safe.

1024
01:26:45.242 --> 01:26:46.576
It's over.

1025
01:26:50.080 --> 01:26:51.873
(Thor inhaling deeply)

1026
01:27:39.129 --> 01:27:41.089
Agent 1: We're spiking.
Agent 2: Levels increase!

1027
01:27:41.339 --> 01:27:43.091
Whosoever holds this hammer.

1028
01:27:45.844 --> 01:27:46.844
if he be worthy.

1029
01:27:50.015 --> 01:27:51.767
shall possess the power of Thor.

1030
01:28:01.151 --> 01:28:02.736
(Mjolnir whooshing)

1031
01:28:07.741 --> 01:28:08.741
Jane!

1032
01:28:11.411 --> 01:28:14.331
- No. No. No!
- Come!

1033
01:28:35.018 --> 01:28:38.313
Oh. My. God.

1034
01:29:48.341 --> 01:29:49.926
So. is this how you normally look?

1035
01:29:50.594 --> 01:29:51.594
More or less.

1036
01:29:52.512 --> 01:29:53.972
It's a good look.

1037
01:29:54.681 --> 01:29:57.726
We must go to the Bifrost site.
I would have words with my brother.

1038
01:29:57.809 --> 01:29:58.935
Coulson: Excuse me!

1039
01:30:02.856 --> 01:30:03.857
Donald?

1040
01:30:05.108 --> 01:30:06.752
I don't think
you've been completely honest with me.

1041
01:30:06.776 --> 01:30:07.903
Know this. son of coul.

1042
01:30:08.278 --> 01:30:11.281
You and I. we fight for the same cause.
the protection of this world.

1043
01:30:11.364 --> 01:30:13.404
From this day fonnard.
you can count me as your ally

1044
01:30:13.450 --> 01:30:16.369
if you return the items
you have taken from Jane.

1045
01:30:16.453 --> 01:30:18.038
- Stolen.
- Borrowed.

1046
01:30:19.122 --> 01:30:21.207
Of course.
you can have your equipment back.

1047
01:30:21.291 --> 01:30:23.168
You're gonna need it
to continue your research.

1048
01:30:24.127 --> 01:30:26.463
Would you like to see
the bridge we spoke of?

1049
01:30:26.755 --> 01:30:28.381
Uh. sure.

1050
01:30:29.841 --> 01:30:30.675
(Exclaims)

1051
01:30:30.759 --> 01:30:32.552
Coulson: Wait. I need to debrief you!

1052
01:30:39.559 --> 01:30:40.936
Welcome to asgard.

1053
01:30:56.159 --> 01:30:57.410
(Muffled straining)

1054
01:31:06.628 --> 01:31:08.797
Heimdall. open the Bifrost.

1055
01:31:16.513 --> 01:31:17.889
Heimdall?

1056
01:31:22.018 --> 01:31:23.353
Heimdall!

1057
01:31:25.480 --> 01:31:26.856
He doesn't answer.

1058
01:31:27.524 --> 01:31:28.942
Then we are stranded.

1059
01:31:29.025 --> 01:31:32.112
Heimdall!
If you can hear me. we need you now!

1060
01:31:32.195 --> 01:31:33.446
(Muffled roaring)

1061
01:31:33.530 --> 01:31:35.615
Thor: Heimdall! We need you now!

1062
01:31:42.205 --> 01:31:43.331
Heimdall!

1063
01:31:58.054 --> 01:32:01.016
I must go back to asgard.
but I give you my word.

1064
01:32:02.392 --> 01:32:04.728
I will return for you.

1065
01:32:12.360 --> 01:32:13.445
Deal?

1066
01:32:27.083 --> 01:32:28.251
Deal.

1067
01:32:44.809 --> 01:32:46.728
Thor: Get him to the healing room!

1068
01:32:48.396 --> 01:32:49.773
Leave my brother to me.

1069
01:33:14.798 --> 01:33:16.299
Laufey: It's said

1070
01:33:16.633 --> 01:33:21.304
you can still hear and see
what transpires around you.

1071
01:33:22.639 --> 01:33:24.808
I hope it's true.

1072
01:33:26.643 --> 01:33:28.603
so that you may know

1073
01:33:29.604 --> 01:33:33.483
your death came at the hand

1074
01:33:34.651 --> 01:33:35.860
of laufey.

1075
01:33:45.120 --> 01:33:47.664
And your death came by the son of Odin.

1076
01:33:48.248 --> 01:33:49.791
(Gasping)

1077
01:33:53.586 --> 01:33:54.586
Loki!

1078
01:33:54.921 --> 01:33:56.506
You saved him!

1079
01:34:00.760 --> 01:34:02.887
I swear to you. mother.

1080
01:34:02.971 --> 01:34:05.515
that they will pay for what
they've done today.

1081
01:34:05.932 --> 01:34:06.932
Thor: Loki.

1082
01:34:07.767 --> 01:34:09.018
Thor!

1083
01:34:09.936 --> 01:34:11.980
I knew you'd return to us.

1084
01:34:17.527 --> 01:34:18.903
Why don't you tell her

1085
01:34:18.987 --> 01:34:22.657
how you sent the destroyer
to kill our friends. to kill me?

1086
01:34:22.740 --> 01:34:23.740
What?

1087
01:34:23.783 --> 01:34:26.202
Why. it must have been enforcing
father's last command.

1088
01:34:26.286 --> 01:34:29.122
You're a talented liar. brother.
Always have been.

1089
01:34:29.873 --> 01:34:30.999
It's good to have you back.

1090
01:34:31.541 --> 01:34:34.627
Now if you'll excuse me.
I have to destroy Jotunheim.

1091
01:35:16.544 --> 01:35:18.004
Loki: You can't stop it.

1092
01:35:18.087 --> 01:35:21.382
The Bifrost will build until
it rips Jotunheim apart.

1093
01:35:27.430 --> 01:35:29.557
(Frost giants screaming)

1094
01:35:43.363 --> 01:35:44.530
Jane?

1095
01:35:46.449 --> 01:35:47.867
Why have you done this?

1096
01:35:48.243 --> 01:35:51.287
To prove to father
that I am the worthy son.

1097
01:35:52.080 --> 01:35:54.540
When he wakes.
I will have saved his life.

1098
01:35:54.958 --> 01:35:57.710
I will have destroyed that
race of monsters.

1099
01:35:57.794 --> 01:35:59.837
And I will be true heir to the throne!

1100
01:36:00.296 --> 01:36:02.215
You can't kill an entire race!

1101
01:36:02.298 --> 01:36:03.716
Why not?

1102
01:36:06.469 --> 01:36:09.639
And what is this newfound love
for the frost giants?

1103
01:36:10.765 --> 01:36:14.060
You could have killed them all
with your bare hands.

1104
01:36:14.143 --> 01:36:16.312
- I've changed.
- So have I.

1105
01:36:18.106 --> 01:36:19.607
Now fight me.

1106
01:36:22.485 --> 01:36:24.320
I never wanted the throne!

1107
01:36:25.613 --> 01:36:27.532
I only ever wanted to be your equal.

1108
01:36:28.574 --> 01:36:30.285
I will not fight you. brother!

1109
01:36:30.368 --> 01:36:31.744
I'm not your brother.

1110
01:36:32.662 --> 01:36:33.913
I never was.

1111
01:36:33.997 --> 01:36:35.540
Loki. this is madness.

1112
01:36:36.165 --> 01:36:37.792
Is it madness?

1113
01:36:38.626 --> 01:36:39.794
Is it?

1114
01:36:41.170 --> 01:36:42.170
Is it?

1115
01:36:43.381 --> 01:36:47.135
Come on. What happened to you
on earth that turned you so soft?

1116
01:36:48.177 --> 01:36:49.846
Don't tell me it was that woman.

1117
01:36:51.097 --> 01:36:52.181
Oh!

1118
01:36:53.016 --> 01:36:54.267
It was!

1119
01:36:54.350 --> 01:36:58.354
Well. maybe. when we're finished here.
I'll pay her a visit myself!

1120
01:36:59.480 --> 01:37:00.815
(Yelling)

1121
01:37:24.464 --> 01:37:25.465
(Laughing)

1122
01:37:40.688 --> 01:37:41.689
Thor!

1123
01:37:49.614 --> 01:37:50.823
Brother. please.

1124
01:37:54.619 --> 01:37:55.912
(Laughing)

1125
01:38:01.918 --> 01:38:03.169
Enough!

1126
01:38:23.731 --> 01:38:24.816
(Grunting)

1127
01:38:34.867 --> 01:38:35.952
(Screaming)

1128
01:38:47.505 --> 01:38:48.548
Look at you.

1129
01:38:51.134 --> 01:38:52.427
the mighty Thor.

1130
01:38:55.513 --> 01:38:57.265
with all your strength.

1131
01:38:58.558 --> 01:39:01.018
and what good does it do you now. huh?

1132
01:39:02.562 --> 01:39:06.149
Do you hear me. brother?
There's nothing you can do!

1133
01:39:24.333 --> 01:39:25.334
What are you doing?

1134
01:39:27.336 --> 01:39:30.673
If you destroy the bridge.
you'll never see her again!

1135
01:39:40.183 --> 01:39:41.559
Forgive me. Jane.

1136
01:39:43.728 --> 01:39:45.563
(Both yelling)

1137
01:40:20.515 --> 01:40:22.350
I could have done it. father!

1138
01:40:23.518 --> 01:40:25.394
I could have done it!

1139
01:40:25.645 --> 01:40:27.063
For you!

1140
01:40:27.813 --> 01:40:29.315
For all of us!

1141
01:40:31.484 --> 01:40:32.818
No. loki.

1142
01:40:41.369 --> 01:40:42.453
Loki. no.

1143
01:41:07.603 --> 01:41:08.896
Jane: It's gone.

1144
01:42:16.339 --> 01:42:18.257
(All laughing)

1145
01:42:21.510 --> 01:42:24.305
And then. with a mighty bellow.

1146
01:42:24.680 --> 01:42:28.768
I flew into the giant metal creature
and laid him low!

1147
01:42:28.851 --> 01:42:32.396
Fandral: Is that another way of saying
you fell on your huge ass?

1148
01:42:32.480 --> 01:42:38.653
Volstagg: As a matter of fact. falling
was a tactic lulling the destroyer...

1149
01:42:52.833 --> 01:42:55.670
My queen. I'm so sorry for your loss.

1150
01:43:01.509 --> 01:43:02.843
Frigga: How is he?

1151
01:43:05.179 --> 01:43:07.181
Sif: He mourns for his brother.

1152
01:43:08.516 --> 01:43:09.684
And...

1153
01:43:10.851 --> 01:43:12.395
He misses her.

1154
01:43:13.396 --> 01:43:14.730
The mortal.

1155
01:43:31.205 --> 01:43:32.915
You'll be a wise king.

1156
01:43:37.378 --> 01:43:39.755
There will never be
a wiser king than you.

1157
01:43:41.215 --> 01:43:42.883
Or a better father.

1158
01:43:53.769 --> 01:43:56.939
I have much to learn.

1159
01:43:58.941 --> 01:44:00.443
I know that now.

1160
01:44:05.448 --> 01:44:07.241
Someday. perhaps.

1161
01:44:08.701 --> 01:44:10.619
I shall make you proud.

1162
01:44:18.252 --> 01:44:20.296
You've already made me proud.

1163
01:44:34.977 --> 01:44:36.979
Thor: So earth is lost to us.

1164
01:44:40.316 --> 01:44:42.109
There is always hope.

1165
01:44:46.322 --> 01:44:47.823
Can you see her?

1166
01:44:48.824 --> 01:44:49.825
(Heimdall laughs)

1167
01:44:50.576 --> 01:44:51.660
Yes.

1168
01:44:55.790 --> 01:44:57.500
Erik: I have the particle detectors!

1169
01:44:57.583 --> 01:44:59.877
Darcy. do you have the S.H.I.E.L.D.
satellite codes?

1170
01:44:59.960 --> 01:45:02.046
Darcy: Yeah. Have you seen my taser?

1171
01:45:02.129 --> 01:45:03.547
Thor: How is she?

1172
01:45:03.631 --> 01:45:05.674
Erik: In the car. Come on. Jane!

1173
01:45:06.008 --> 01:45:08.135
Heimdall: She searches for you.

1174
01:53:17.666 --> 01:53:19.626
Nick fury: Dr. Selvig.

1175
01:53:22.462 --> 01:53:24.631
So you're the man behind all this?

1176
01:53:26.800 --> 01:53:28.844
It's quite a labyrinth.

1177
01:53:29.511 --> 01:53:32.931
I was thinking
they're taking me down here to kill me.

1178
01:53:40.647 --> 01:53:43.442
I've been hearing
about the new Mexico situation.

1179
01:53:44.401 --> 01:53:48.030
Your work has impressed a lot of people
who are much smarter than I am.

1180
01:53:48.113 --> 01:53:50.198
I have a lot to work with.

1181
01:53:50.824 --> 01:53:54.119
The foster theory.
A gateway to another dimension.

1182
01:53:54.786 --> 01:53:55.954
It's unprecedented.

1183
01:53:58.498 --> 01:53:59.498
Isn't it?

1184
01:54:03.170 --> 01:54:06.506
Legend tells us one thing.
history. another.

1185
01:54:06.840 --> 01:54:10.927
But every now and then.
we find something that belongs to both.

1186
01:54:18.852 --> 01:54:19.728
What is it?

1187
01:54:19.811 --> 01:54:20.854
Power. doctor.

1188
01:54:21.563 --> 01:54:23.440
If we can figure out how to tap it.

1189
01:54:24.024 --> 01:54:25.359
maybe unlimited power.

1190
01:54:31.239 --> 01:54:33.408
Well. I guess that's worth a look.

1191
01:54:35.243 --> 01:54:37.537
Well. I guess that's worth a look.
